documentation.text: @dev Pauses the creation of new debt contracts during a tau cycle to process new debt applications
@dev Unpauses the system after the tau cycles finnishes

@dev Sets the system interest rate
 @param _systemInterestRate The new system interest rate, in basis points

@dev Grants the QLE role to the specified address.
 @param _qle The address to grant the QLE role to.

@dev Processes a payment for the specified debt contract and sets the present value of the PDC. 
 @param id The ID of the debt contract to process the payment for.

Paused(address).details: Emitted when the pause is triggered by `account`.

RoleAdminChanged(bytes32,bytes32,bytes32.details: Emitted when `newAdminRole` is set as ``role``'s admin role, replacing `previousAdminRole` `DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE` is the starting admin for all roles, despite {RoleAdminChanged} not being emitted signaling this. _Available since v3.1._

RoleGranted(bytes32,address,address).details: Emitted when `account` is granted `role`. `sender` is the account that originated the contract call, an admin role bearer except when using {AccessControl-_setupRole}.

RoleRevoked(bytes32,address,address).details: Emitted when `account` is revoked `role`. `sender` is the account that originated the contract call:   - if using `revokeRole`, it is the admin role bearer   - if using `renounceRole`, it is the role bearer (i.e. `account`)

Unpaused(address).details: Emitted when the pause is lifted by `account`.

calculateDebtContractValue(uint256).details: Calculates the current value of a debt contract

params.id: The ID of the debt contract to calculate the value of

returns._0: The current value of the debt contract

calculateNextPayment(uint256).details: Calculates the next payment for a given debt contract, based on the current state and the interest rate

params.id: The id of the debt contract to calculate the next payment for

createDebtContract(address,int256,int256.details: Creates a new debt contract and stores it in the `debtContracts` mapping.

params.interestRateMultiplier: The interest rate multiplier for the loan. Will be multiplied with 0.01. So 100% -> 100 (equal to systemInterestRate)
params.principalTotal: The total principal of the loan, as a SD59x18 number.
params.totalPaymentPeriods: The total number of payment periods for the loan, as a SD59x18 number.

returns._0: ID nonce of the new debt contract.

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantQLERole(address).details: Grants the QLE role to the specified address.

params._qle: The address to grant the QLE role to.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pauseSystem().details: Pauses the creation of new debt contracts during a tau cycle to process new debt applications

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

pay(uint256).details: Processes a payment for the specified debt contract and sets the present value of the PDC.

params.id: The ID of the debt contract to process the payment for.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

params._systemInterestRate: The new system interest rate, in basis points

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unpauseSystem().details: Unpauses the system after the tau cycles finnishes

PRBMath_MulDiv18_Overflow(uint256,uint25.notice: Emitted when the ending result in the fixed-point version of `mulDiv` would overflow uint256.

PRBMath_MulDiv_Overflow(uint256,uint256,.notice: Emitted when the ending result in `mulDiv` would overflow uint256.

PRBMath_SD59x18_Abs_MinSD59x18().notice: Emitted when taking the absolute value of `MIN_SD59x18`.

PRBMath_SD59x18_Convert_Overflow(int256).notice: Emitted when converting a basic integer to the fixed-point format overflows SD59x18.

PRBMath_SD59x18_Convert_Underflow(int256.notice: Emitted when converting a basic integer to the fixed-point format underflows SD59x18.

PRBMath_SD59x18_Div_InputTooSmall().notice: Emitted when dividing two numbers and one of them is `MIN_SD59x18`.

PRBMath_SD59x18_Div_Overflow(int256,int2.notice: Emitted when dividing two numbers and one of the intermediary unsigned results overflows SD59x18.

PRBMath_SD59x18_Exp2_InputTooBig(int256).notice: Emitted when taking the binary exponent of a base greater than 192.

PRBMath_SD59x18_IntoUint256_Underflow(in.notice: Emitted when trying to cast an UD60x18 number that doesn't fit in uint256.

PRBMath_SD59x18_Log_InputTooSmall(int256.notice: Emitted when taking the logarithm of a number less than or equal to zero.

PRBMath_SD59x18_Mul_InputTooSmall().notice: Emitted when multiplying two numbers and one of the inputs is `MIN_SD59x18`.

PRBMath_SD59x18_Mul_Overflow(int256,int2.notice: Emitted when multiplying two numbers and the intermediary absolute result overflows SD59x18.

PRBMath_SD59x18_Powu_Overflow(int256,uin.notice: Emitted when raising a number to a power and hte intermediary absolute result overflows SD59x18.
